    public interface FunctionIntf
extends java.io.Serializable
    interface defining a function mapping objects of some domain (not necessarily R^n) to R. The interface is also asked to implement Serializable so that function objects can be transported over sockets and executed in remote JVMs.

      • eval

        double eval(java.lang.Object arg,
            java.util.HashMap params)
     throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        the method mapping the arg passed in to a number in R. Any parameters are passed in the params HashMap.
        Parameters:
        arg - Object
        params - HashMap
        Returns:
        double Notice that it is illegal for the function to return Double.NaN; if the argument is outside the domain of the function definition an IllegalArgumentException should be thrown instead. It is valid though to return Double.[POSITIVE|NEGATIVE]_INFINITY.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the arg is illegal for the function
